# Reusable Components

## Rule
When the same HTML/view structure appears (or would appear) in more than one screen, extract it into a shared component in `screens/` (like `StepIndicator` or `StepNav`). Never copy-paste a view block across multiple screens.

## How to Check
Before writing view code in a screen, scan existing shared components for something that already fits. If nothing exists and you see the same pattern needed in 2+ screens, create a new `object` with a polymorphic `apply[Msg](...)` method.

## Pattern

```scala
// screens/MySharedWidget.scala
object MySharedWidget:
  def apply[Msg](label: String, onAction: Msg, enabled: Boolean): Html[Msg] =
    div(`class` := "widget")(
      button(`class` := (if enabled then "btn" else "btn btn-disabled"), onClick(onAction))(text(label))
    )
```

Then in each screen: `MySharedWidget("Go", MyMsg.Go, isReady)` — one line, not a duplicated block.

## Existing Shared Components
| Component | File | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `StepIndicator` | `screens/StepIndicator.scala` | Wizard progress bar |
| `StepNav` | `screens/StepNav.scala` | Back / Next navigation row |
| `ScreenHeader` | `screens/ScreenHeader.scala` | Shared screen header |
| `GalleryLayout` | `screens/GalleryLayout.scala` | Card grid with empty state |
